The Black Sash has noted Social Development Minister Lindiwe Zulu’s directive that South African Social Security Agency’s (Sassa) offices, pay points and Post Office branches must remain open for next month’s grant payments. But, said the organisation, only 5% of grant beneficiaries use pay points and Post Office branches. What is outside Zulu’s scope are 95% of the 12 million grant recipients who collect their grants at ATMs (61%) and retailers (34%). “Strategies for containing the spread of the virus in these commercial spaces should be communicated timeously. The measures must take into account that there are about 3.6 million...